explanation: This access requirement has an ACL with specific principals (users or teams) who have permissions to manage it. The ACL defines who can review access requests, grant or deny access, and modify the requirement settings.

This access requirement has an ACL that grants management permissions to designated administrators. These administrators can review and approve access requests from users who want to access the associated data.
The ACL for this access requirement specifies which users or teams have administrative control. These principals can manage the access requirement including reviewing requests and updating terms.
This access requirement has designated managers defined in its ACL. The ACL grants these principals the authority to oversee access requests and maintain the requirement.
An ACL is configured for this access requirement with resource access entries that define who can administer it. These administrators have permissions to manage access request workflows.
